Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice half the @red onion{1}. Halve @lime{1}. Drain @cannellini beans{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine sliced onion, juice from whole lime, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cover with #plastic wrap{} and microwave for ~{30%seconds}; stir to combine. Set aside to pickle.

> Use whole onion for 4 servings. Use both limes for 4 servings.

Heat a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @pulled pork{8%ounces}; cook, breaking up pork into pieces, until warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add @BBQ sauce{1/2%cup} and beans; cook, stirring occasionally, until pork and beans are coated, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Meanwhile, wrap @whole wheat pitas{2} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{15-30%seconds}; halve crosswise.

Fill each pita pocket with pork and beans, cilantro, and as much pickled onion as you like (draining first). Divide between plates and serve.

> Pulled Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.